5.2 Key Algorithms

5.2.1 Adaptive Pheromone Optimization (APO)

Our novel extension of ant colony optimization that adapts evaporation rates based on problem dynamics:

```python
class AdaptivePheromoneOptimizer:
    def optimize(self, problem, initial_config):
        pheromone_map = PheromoneMap(problem.dimensions)
        
        for iteration in range(self.max_iterations):
            # Adaptive evaporation rate
            evaporation_rate = self.calculate_adaptive_rate(
                iteration, 
                problem.complexity,
                convergence_rate
            )
            
            # Parallel agent exploration
            solutions = self.explore_parallel(problem, pheromone_map)
            
            # Update pheromones with quality-weighted deposits
            self.update_pheromones(pheromone_map, solutions, evaporation_rate)
            
            # Dynamic population adjustment
            if self.has_converged(pheromone_map):
                self.increase_exploration()
            else:
                self.increase_exploitation()
        
        return self.extract_solution(pheromone_map)
```

5.2.2 Meta-Learning with Adversarial Constraints (MLAC)

A novel meta-learning approach that intentionally tests boundary conditions:

```python
class MetaLearningAdversarial:
    def learn(self, task_distribution):
        # Base model training
        base_model = self.train_base_model(task_distribution)
        
        # Generate adversarial tasks by constraint inversion
        adversarial_tasks = self.generate_adversarial_tasks(task_distribution)
        
        # Meta-training on mixed task distribution
        meta_model = self.meta_train(base_model, adversarial_tasks)
        
        # Adaptation capability testing
        adaptation_scores = self.test_adaptation(meta_model, novel_tasks)
        
        return MetaLearnedModel(meta_model, adaptation_scores)
```

