6. Governance & Ethics Framework

6.1 Ethical Principles

Our system operates under seven core principles:

1. Human Sovereignty: AI augments but never replaces human decision-making
2. Distributed Benefit: Solutions must benefit all stakeholders, not just privileged groups
3. Planetary Stewardship: Operations respect planetary boundaries
4. Transparency: Decisions must be explainable and auditable
5. Privacy by Design: Personal data protection built into architecture
6. Fail-Safe Design: Systems degrade gracefully, never catastrophically
7. Intergenerational Justice: Consider impacts on future generations

6.2 Governance Structure

```
Global Governance Board
├── Technical Oversight Committee
├── Ethical Review Board
├── Domain Expert Councils (Climate, Health, Urban, Enterprise)
├── Community Advisory Panels
└── Independent Audit Team
```

6.3 Safety Mechanisms

Stallion Safety:

· Time-limited emergency powers
· Human override requirement for critical decisions
· Multi-party authorization for resource allocation

Ant Safety:

· Differential privacy in all distributed computations
· Opt-in participation for personal data
· Regular algorithmic fairness audits

Crow Safety:

· Precautionary principle for novel interventions
· Adversarial testing of all predictions
· Transparency requirements for model decisions

6.4 Regulatory Compliance

The system is designed to comply with:

· GDPR, CCPA, and emerging global privacy regulations
· AI ethics guidelines from EU, OECD, and IEEE
· Domain-specific regulations (HIPAA, environmental laws)
· International human rights frameworks

